Every time I visit Singapore I stay at the Swisshotel, 40th floor or higher! You'd be amazed what you can see from the outdoor deck on the 43rd floor! On this day a couple of workers were performing maintenance on the Esplanade Performing Arts Center and as luck would have it I had returned to my room shortly after lunch ONLY to change shirts when I glanced outside and across the way, in the direction of the Marina, there they were. I immediately mounted the Nikkor 200-500 and D810 on the tripod and here is one of several shots!
